    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-06-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/166.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gummeré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my telegram to the
                    department of this date.<note n="1" xml:id="d610fn1">Supra.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In explanation of the above, I have the honor to report that couriers arrived
                    this morning from Tetuan with letters announcing that the Pretender Mulai Hafid
                    had been proclaimed as Sultan at Tetuan on the 17th instant, amid the rejoicings
                    of the populace, the town remaining tranquil. Everything is still quiet at
                    Tangier, but the people are pleased with the successes of Mulai Hafid.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">S. R. Gummeré.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
